Mindful of the ["7 Meta Questions"][1] banner up there for the beta, I thought this might also help in answering the question of what is on or off topic.

A course at work on this type of thing encouraged us to structure the pitch in terms of the following four components:

 - Customer ("Questioner" in this case);
 - Issue;
 - Feel;
 - Outcome;

Example:  I am interested in how economics influences the world but concerned that I know less about how it works than I would like and through this site able to gain expert knowledge on topics as diverse as the way money works and where demand actually comes from.

Probably a bit "marketing-speak" but it needs to be that short.  What are your ideas?


  [1]: http://blog.stackoverflow.com/2010/07/the-7-essential-meta-questions-of-every-beta/
